To me pretty much all of those "solutions" are incredibly lazy and come from a place of actively not wanting humans to be at the top. >>39042011
The issue with this is that human promiscuity doesn't come from us simply not naturally mating for life, it comes from us being naturally inclined towards promiscuity. In a natural setting humans are one of the most promiscuous species on the planet. Primates are one of the most promiscuous animal groups on the planet. Despite that, we've consistently become monogamous as we've advanced. In fact monogamy has been critical and intertwined with civilization as we know it. That's why people say anthros would be less promiscuous. Not because they're naturally monogamous, but because most of them don't have a natural inclination towards promiscuity like humans do.
